But among the signs of hope, a
rise in citizen
efforts to take part in the
nation's political

39:58.829 --> 40:00.564 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and cultural life.

40:00.598 --> 40:01.665 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has our story.

40:01.699 --> 40:05.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of his ongoing series
Culture at
Risk.

40:05.136 --> 40:12.076 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The Medina of
Tunis, the old
center of the city, dating back
to the seventh

40:12.109 --> 40:19.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
century, its narrow walkways,
vibrant colors,
and grand architecture evoke a
rich past.

40:19.683 --> 40:25.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now nestled within a sprawling
modern city,
the Medina remains a home to
some 100,000

40:25.723 --> 40:33.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
residents, 15,000 homes, 700
monuments, and
abundant commerce within its
sprawling souks,

40:33.164 --> 40:34.865 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
or markets.

40:34.899 --> 40:38.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For hundreds of years, places
like this were
the heart of life in the Arab
world.

40:38.669 --> 40:48.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The question today is how to
preserve something
of that old character, even as
the society

40:48.913 --> 40:52.516 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
around them changes.

40:52.550 --> 40:57.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Architect Zoubeir Mouhli grew up
here in the
Medina, and now heads an
organization to preserve

40:57.455 --> 40:59.256 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it.

40:59.290 --> 41:01.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ZOUBEIR MOUHLI, Association for
the Preservation
of the Medina (through
translator): When I

41:01.125 --> 41:04.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was a student, I dreamed of
working in the
Medina because I knew there were
so many hidden

41:04.361 --> 41:06.797 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things people didn't know about
that are incredibly
valuable.

41:06.831 --> 41:12.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: For him, this
place represents
a way of life, an alternative to
the modern

41:12.169 --> 41:13.437 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
city.

41:13.471 --> 41:15.606 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ZOUBEIR MOUHLI (through
translator): There
is no soul there.

41:15.639 --> 41:19.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Everything is done for the cars,
not for the
people, not for the pedestrians,
not for the

41:19.710 --> 41:23.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people who want to see each
other, to talk
to each other, to go and have a
coffee together.

41:23.781 --> 41:25.516 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
All this is so important to me.

41:25.549 --> 41:30.321 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Dramatic change
came to the
Medina starting in the 1950s, as
the era of

41:30.354 --> 41:32.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
French rule ended.

41:32.189 --> 41:36.827 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Many laborers from the
countryside moved in
seeking work, while elites and
those with

41:36.861 --> 41:41.365 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
means left for the new suburbs,
which continue
to develop today.

41:41.398 --> 41:44.368 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Medina was ignored, and
slowly decayed.

41:44.401 --> 41:49.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ZOUBEIR MOUHLI (through
translator): The Medina
was considered an archaic space
that was contrary

41:49.840 --> 41:54.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the country's modernization,
and even the
cause of our underdevelopment
and the reason

41:54.378 --> 41:56.080 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for the French protectorate.

41:56.113 --> 42:01.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: By the time the
Medina was
added to a U.N. list of places
of special

42:01.151 --> 42:08.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
cultural importance in 1979,
more than half
its buildings were in disrepair
or ruins.

42:08.225 --> 42:11.529 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But changes in the country are
also changing
the Medina.

42:11.562 --> 42:18.502 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In late 2010, a Tunisian fruit
vendor set
himself ablaze, setting off a
chain of protests

42:18.536 --> 42:23.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that overturned the country's
dictator, Abidine
Ben Ali, and spread across the
region as the

42:23.641 --> 42:25.843 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Arab Spring.

42:25.876 --> 42:30.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tunisia has been the only
country thus far
to successfully transition out
of protests

42:30.614 --> 42:32.917 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
into a democracy.

42:32.950 --> 42:38.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Among much else, that unleashed
new civic
pride and an interest in
preserving the country's

42:38.255 --> 42:42.793 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
culture, one influenced by
Roman, Ottoman,
Arabic and European traditions.

42:42.826 --> 42:45.663 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LEILA BEN GACEM, Tunisia: This
house was on
sale in 2006.

42:45.696 --> 42:48.999 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I bought it from a family that
lived here
for 300 years.

42:49.033 --> 42:50.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Three hundred?

42:50.034 --> 42:51.869 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LEILA BEN GACEM: Yes.

42:51.902 --> 42:55.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: For Leila Ben
Gacem, that meant
rehabilitating an old home to
turn it into

42:55.773 --> 43:02.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a boutique hotel, a project that
required
working with local artisans,
tile specialists,

43:02.413 --> 43:07.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
woodworkers, gypsum carvers, who
understood
the materials and artistic
styles.

43:07.418 --> 43:11.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEILA BEN GACEM: These stones
could be recycled
from the destroyed site of
Carthage.

43:11.655 --> 43:15.526 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You mean the
ancient archaeological
site of Carthage, yes, not far
from us.

43:15.559 --> 43:16.527 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LEILA BEN GACEM: Yes.

43:16.560 --> 43:19.997 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The tiles could have came with
the Andalusians.

43:20.030 --> 43:21.832 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes, in Spain.

43:21.865 --> 43:22.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LEILA BEN GACEM: In Spain.

43:22.866 --> 43:25.102 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The arches could have came from
the Ottomans.

43:25.135 --> 43:28.105 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So it's the blend that makes
Tunisia today.

43:28.138 --> 43:30.140 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It was difficult
work.

43:30.174 --> 43:34.945 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The house had to be entirely
retrofitted with
modern plumbing and electricity.

43:34.979 --> 43:36.413 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Not a good place for a car.

43:36.447 --> 43:40.117 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LEILA BEN GACEM: No, that's why
taxi drivers
hate to drive in here.

43:40.150 --> 43:45.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And the area
faces all kinds
of challenges, including
maintaining enough

43:45.155 --> 43:49.660 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
infrastructure to hold onto old
businesses
and attract new investment.

43:49.693 --> 43:55.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEILA BEN GACEM: Since the birth
of the Medina
in the seventh century, eighth
century, there

43:55.299 --> 43:59.670 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
always been an ecosystem of
traders, of artisans,
of businesses.

43:59.703 --> 44:03.173 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So the trading sectors change
with time.

44:03.207 --> 44:09.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think to convert the
Medina into a cultural
artistic destination, that needs
a whole new

44:09.446 --> 44:11.649 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ecosystem to be developed now.

44:11.682 --> 44:14.652 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Ben Gacem's doing
her part.

44:14.685 --> 44:19.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's already working on a
second guest house
and has opened a workspace
nearby to help

44:19.590 --> 44:24.328 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
transfer some of the skills
being lost.

44:24.361 --> 44:30.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Saturday mornings, there's a
calligraphy
class and next door a workshop
on bookbinding,

44:30.167 --> 44:34.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
taught by Mohamed Ben Sassi,
whose shop is
just down the street.

44:34.705 --> 44:39.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's thought to be the last
bookbinder working
in the Medina, and is eager to
reach a new

44:39.677 --> 44:41.278 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
generation.

44:41.311 --> 44:43.647 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MOHAMED BEN SASSI, Tunisia
(through translator):
There is nobody, no one left.

44:43.681 --> 44:50.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For 40 years, I worked in the
national library,
and there was nobody to do this
job, 40 years.

44:50.187 --> 44:51.488 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The book will never go away.

44:51.522 --> 44:54.758 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It has witnessed many gales and
thunderbolts
and disasters.

44:54.792 --> 44:56.560 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is still here.

44:56.593 --> 45:01.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Up the street is
a beautiful,
but dilapidated building called
La Rachidia,

45:01.932 --> 45:06.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
opened in the 1930s and once one
of the most
famous concert venues in North
Africa.

45:06.937 --> 45:12.710 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Here, volunteers are digitizing
sheet music,
historical documents, concert
posters and

45:12.743 --> 45:24.755 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
photographs found sitting in
boxes, saving
traditional Tunisian music known
as malouf.

45:24.788 --> 45:29.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then there's a project
called MedinaPedia
in the belly of an old Christian
church, where

45:29.927 --> 45:35.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
another group of volunteers is
documenting
every building and monument in
the area, researching

45:35.632 --> 45:42.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
famous residents, and uploading
that information
to Wikipedia, a variety of
projects, committed

45:42.506 --> 45:44.742 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
people, young and old.

45:44.775 --> 45:49.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Everyone we spoke to said it
will be important
to move forward in a way that
maintains the

45:49.213 --> 45:54.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
character and the inhabitants of
the Medina,
even while trying to attract
tourists to a

45:54.218 --> 45:59.123 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country in desperate need of the
economic
boost they bring.

45:59.156 --> 46:04.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Despite the many challenges the
government
here faces, Leila Ben Gacem says
cultural

46:04.061 --> 46:06.830 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
heritage should continue to be
one of its
priorities.

46:06.864 --> 46:11.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEILA BEN GACEM: The government
underestimates
the potential of heritage and
culture in creating

46:12.002 --> 46:17.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
opportunities, and maybe they
even think of
it as something for elite or
something as

46:17.074 --> 46:18.876 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a luxury.

46:18.909 --> 46:24.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the meantime, civil society
is very active
today in investing, investing
time, money,

46:24.882 --> 46:31.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
energy, advocacy to restore such
beautiful
spaces and bring back the magic
to the Medina.

46:31.155 --> 46:35.192 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A magic found in
every tile
and stone.

46:35.225 --> 46:44.968 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Jeffrey Brown
in the Medina of Tunis.

46:45.002 --> 46:52.609 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to something
sweet.

46:52.643 --> 46:56.246 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
More often than not, a dessert
is better when
you share it.

46:56.280 --> 47:00.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's the thinking of one man
who uses baking
to reach out to his community.

47:00.317 --> 47:05.656 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
From PBS station NET in
Nebraska, Dennis Kellogg
explains.

47:05.689 --> 47:10.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: If you're
looking for a good
dessert in Hastings, you can
find plenty of

47:10.794 --> 47:13.063 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
places to get a sweet treat.

47:13.096 --> 47:18.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But some of the city's tastiest
pies and cakes
come from the kitchen of this
small home,

47:18.669 --> 47:21.972 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
where Leo Kellner has lived for
more than
six decades.

47:22.005 --> 47:23.574 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WOMAN: ®MDNM /Thank you, Leo.

47:23.607 --> 47:25.209 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: ®MDNM /Thank you, Leo.

47:25.242 --> 47:27.945 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WOMAN: Red velvet is my
favorite.

47:27.978 --> 47:34.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: The doorbell
seems to be always
ringing here, as friends stop by
to pick up

47:34.651 --> 47:37.020 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
one of Leo's culinary creations.

47:37.054 --> 47:39.256 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: Thank you so much for
making this cake.

47:39.289 --> 47:41.124 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: Thank you again.

47:41.158 --> 47:48.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: Leo spends his
days in the
kitchen, gladly baking hundreds
of pies and

47:48.432 --> 47:50.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
cakes every year.

47:50.167 --> 47:55.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEO KELLNER, Baker: My crust is
flaky, and
tastes like -- more or less like
a cookie.

47:55.439 --> 47:58.642 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: And Leo Kellner
is 98-years-old.

47:58.675 --> 48:04.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LEO KELLNER: I have got to have
something
to do.

48:04.181 --> 48:07.417 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I would be dead if I wouldn't be
doing this.

48:07.451 --> 48:12.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I lay at night in bed and think
how I can
change things, make things
better.

48:12.522 --> 48:18.495 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have changed my pie three
times, the apple
pie.

48:18.528 --> 48:24.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: Leo grew up
during tough times
in the 1930s, watching his mom
and sister

48:24.735 --> 48:27.604 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bake with whatever ingredients
they happened
to have.

48:27.638 --> 48:32.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He spent a lifetime working with
irrigation
and grain-drying businesses.

48:32.843 --> 48:35.746 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He didn't retire until he was
92.

48:35.779 --> 48:40.951 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's when Madelon, his wife of
72 years,
got sick and passed away.

48:40.984 --> 48:45.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LEO KELLNER: I started about
four months or
so after my wife died.

48:45.522 --> 48:49.493 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I was sitting here not knowing
what to do
with myself.

48:49.526 --> 48:52.829 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I was used to working.

48:52.863 --> 48:58.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I had given up what I was
doing, was kind
of sitting here in the house and
I said to

48:58.635 --> 49:00.637 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
myself, I can bake.

49:00.671 --> 49:06.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: He made 144
apple pies that
first year, and hasn't stopped
since.

49:06.810 --> 49:12.249 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You might think it provides a
great retirement
income for Leo, but the thing
is, he doesn't

49:12.282 --> 49:14.084 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
charge a cent.

49:14.117 --> 49:19.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He gives every one of his pies
and cakes away
for free to friends, those who
are sick, or

49:19.523 --> 49:26.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to hospice volunteers, to those
attending
a funeral, to an elderly woman
or a man who

49:26.763 --> 49:28.498 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
just can't afford a good meal.

49:28.532 --> 49:33.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEO KELLNER: You don't know what
that means
to a person, unless you have
been poor, like

49:33.971 --> 49:38.308 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I was years ago.

49:38.342 --> 49:41.378 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I would have been so tickled.

49:41.411 --> 49:46.817 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And my folks couldn't even give
me a pie or
a cake or something.

49:46.850 --> 49:51.121 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So I lived that life.

49:51.154 --> 49:59.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's why I am happy when I
can help
somebody put a smile on their
face.

49:59.463 --> 50:05.068 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MADDY MUSICH, 12 Years Old: Hey,
Leo.

50:05.102 --> 50:09.639 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: Leo is even
building a pie-making
legacy.

50:09.673 --> 50:15.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's mentoring 12-year-old Maddy
Musich, teaching
her how to bake, because, as Leo
puts it,

50:15.512 --> 50:19.716 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
girls today need to know more
than just how
to run a computer.

50:19.750 --> 50:25.822 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MADDY MUSICH: He's like my other
grandpa,
kind of.

50:25.856 --> 50:29.359 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I get older, I want to bake
for my kids
and teach them how to do it.

50:29.393 --> 50:32.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And even if they don't like it,
who doesn't
love food anyway?

50:32.462 --> 50:38.068 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LEO KELLNER: I consider her just
more than
a friend, like part of me.

50:38.101 --> 50:42.739 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I go, I want her to take
over where I
left off.

50:42.773 --> 50:46.109 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And I think she will.

50:46.143 --> 50:52.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENNIS KELLOGG: He can share his
recipes with
Maddy, but she will soon learn
Leo adds something

50:52.349 --> 50:56.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to his pies and cakes that you
can't buy in
a grocery store.

